Adnan Jakubovic was born on 11.11.1986 in the city of Tuzla, Bosnia and Herzegovina. His first interest in electronic music was around the time the war was over, 1997. The first CD that he has purchased was from Prodigy "Music for jilted generation". After that he slowly came into contact with the production of: Chemical Brothers, Propellerheads, Astral Projection etc. Also he enjoyed in music of: Depeche Mode, Massive Attack, Moby, Tool, Radiohead and pioneer of Bosnian electronic music Adi Lukovac. DJ, producer and vocalist Eve Falcon has become a premier name in progressive breaks & house throughout the U.S. and the world. She was featured in URB Magazine for their highly regarded "Next 100" issue, and BPM Magazine declared Eve a winner in their Next On The Decks competition.
